'''Leon [[baron]] Bekaert''' (born 1958) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman. He started his career in 1983 as Managing Partner of Pauli Philippines ([[Manila]]) and in 1984 transferred in 1984 to P.T. LVD Indonesia as Managing Director. In 1987 he joined the [[Bekaert|Bekaert Group]] as Sales Manager Bekaert [[Hong Kong]] and in 1989 he was appointed as Strategic Project Manager and in 1991 Product Manager Fencing Products. Leon Bekaert left the Beakert Group in 1994 and became a member of the Board. He holds a degree in Applied Economics from the [[Katholieke Universiteit Leuven]] (1983) and obtained an [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] at the [[International Institute for Management Development|IMI]] in [[Geneva]] in 1987. With an estimated fortune of 761 million [[euro]] he is one of the wealthiest people in Belgium.
